{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-awesome-readme-js","path":"/andrewda/awesome-frc/readme/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Track Awesome List"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"01670127-3849-5e10-be72-da6b07c58507","html":"<h1 id=\"awesome-frc-awesome\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#awesome-frc-awesome\" aria-label=\"awesome frc awesome permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Awesome FRC <a href=\"https://awesome.re\"><img src=\"https://awesome.re/badge.svg\" alt=\"Awesome\"></a></h1>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.firstinspires.org/robotics/frc\"><img src=\"https://github.com/andrewda/awesome-frc/raw/master/media/first.svg\" align=\"right\" width=\"150\"></a></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>A curated list of <em>awesome</em> packages and resources related to the FIRST Robotics Competition.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.firstinspires.org/robotics/frc\">FRC</a> is a global High School robotics competition in which students compete to build the best robot possible in just six weeks. These tools, resources, communities, and learning materials will help make your FRC season a blast.</p>\n<h2 id=\"contents\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#contents\" aria-label=\"contents permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Contents</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#general\">General</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#suppliers\">Suppliers</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#programming\">Programming</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#vision\">Vision</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#scouting\">Scouting</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#driving\">Driving</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#community\">Community</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#repositories\">Repositories</a>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#javakotlin\">Java/Kotlin</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#c\">C++</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#c-1\">C#</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#python\">Python</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#css\">CSS</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#ruby\">Ruby</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><a href=\"#videos\">Videos</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#miscellaneous\">Miscellaneous</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"general\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#general\" aria-label=\"general permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>General</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/MC42/FRCPenultimateManual\">FRC Penultimate Manual</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/MC42/FRCPenultimateManual\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">18</span></span></a> - All-in-one manual for FRC teams and team members.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.thebluealliance.com/\">The Blue Alliance</a> - FRC's leading event, team, and match tracker.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.thecompassalliance.org/\">The Compass Alliance</a> - A resource for learning about all FRC topic, made for any level of experience.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/calcmogul/state-space-guide\">State Space Guide</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/calcmogul/state-space-guide\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">142</span></span></a> - A practical guide to state-space control: graduate-level control theory for high schoolers.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/wpilibsuite/GradleRIO\">GradleRIO</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/wpilibsuite/GradleRIO\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">232</span></span></a> - A powerful Gradle Plugin that allows teams competing in the FIRST robotics competition to produce and build their code.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"suppliers\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#suppliers\" aria-label=\"suppliers permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Suppliers</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.ctr-electronics.com/\">CTR Electronics</a> - Supplier of many popular parts certified for FRC use, including the Talon SRX's and Victor SPX's.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.andymark.com/\">AndyMark</a> - A supplier for the educational robotics market, focusing particularly on FIRST.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.vexrobotics.com/vexpro\">VEXpro</a> - A distributor of parts for FRC, FTC, and VEX formed by FIRST alumni.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.mcmaster.com/\">McMaster-Carr</a> - A comprehensive index of parts for many applications, from fasteners to pneumatics.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.revrobotics.com/\">REV Robotics</a> - Distributor of many FIRST Legal mechanical and electrical parts, including NEO Brushless Motors and Spark MAX Motor Controllers.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.wcproducts.net\">West Coast Products</a> - A company founded by FIRST alumni that aims to distribute reliable and high-quality parts.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"programming\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#programming\" aria-label=\"programming permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Programming</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://frc-pdr.readthedocs.io/en/latest/\">FRC Programming Done Right</a> - Exhaustive and well-written guide to programming in FRC, the right way.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://wpilib.screenstepslive.com\">WPILib ScreenSteps</a> - Old and unsupported documentation for hardware and officially supported software languages. For up to date, check below.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.wpilib.org/en/latest/\">WPILib Docs</a> - Up-to-date documentation on FRC hardware and software for 2020 and beyond.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"vision\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#vision\" aria-label=\"vision permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Vision</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/wpilibsuite/cscore\">CSCore</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/wpilibsuite/cscore\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">24</span></span></a> - The CScore camera vision library from WPI.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rLwOkAJqImo\">254 2016 Vision Talk</a> - The most complete lesson about vision tracking out there.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/2729StormRobotics/StormCV2017\">2729 Storm Robotics Vision</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/2729StormRobotics/StormCV2017\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">5</span></span></a> - An example of using OpenCV and GRIP to create a vision system.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://limelightvision.io/\">Limelight</a> - A plug-and-play vision solution built for FRC.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/team3997/ChickenVision\">ChickenVision</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/team3997/ChickenVision\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">31</span></span></a> - An easy to implement vision system created by Team 3997.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"scouting\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#scouting\" aria-label=\"scouting permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Scouting</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/SUPERCILEX/Robot-Scouter\">Robot Scouter</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/SUPERCILEX/Robot-Scouter\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">94</span></span></a> - Gorgeous and powerful Android scouting app.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/FRCScout/FRCScout\">VictiScout</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/FRCScout/FRCScout\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">18</span></span></a> - Light Electron scouting app by Team 1418.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"driving\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#driving\" aria-label=\"driving permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Driving</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/FRC-Utilities/QDriverStation\">QDriverStation</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/FRC-Utilities/QDriverStation\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">131</span></span></a> - Popular open-source Driver Station clone for all Desktop platforms. Though not permitted in competition, essential for teams wishing to drive on another platform or up their open source cred.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/FRCDashboard/FRCDashboard\">FRCDashboard</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/FRCDashboard/FRCDashboard\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">122</span></span></a> - Powerful and flexible boilerplate for creating complex driving dashboards with web technologies.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/erikuhlmann/SmartDashboard.js\">SmartDashboard.js</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/erikuhlmann/SmartDashboard.js\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">14</span></span></a> - SmartDashboard port written in JavaScript with <code class=\"language-text\">nw.js</code>.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"community\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#community\" aria-label=\"community permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Community</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/FRC/\">/r/FRC</a> - The one and only FRC subreddit.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.chiefdelphi.com/forums/portal.php\">Chief Delphi</a> - The essential forum for all things FRC.</li>\n<li><a h